# Patch 0005 — Per-workspace setting overrides (Kavacha Workspace Identities, Phase 2).
#
# What: adds an optional `settings` object to Zen's space object, holding a
# CURATED set of per-space overrides applied at the workspace-switch
# chokepoint: website color scheme (light/dark/default), block-all media
# autoplay, block notification prompts, offer-to-save passwords, and search
# suggestions. A "Workspace Settings" submenu in the space actions menu edits
# them; "Reset to Browser Defaults" clears the object.
# Safety semantics: the key set is a deliberate allowlist
# (KAVACHA_SPACE_SETTINGS) — workspaces sync across devices, so arbitrary
# pref control would let a synced payload flip security-critical prefs.
# The kavacha.workspaces.settings-baseline pref records the profile's value
# before the first override of each key; spaces without that override
# restore it (same pattern as the search-engine baseline).
# Why a patch: same switch chokepoint and menu as 0003/0004; the field
# persists + syncs for free through Zen's session store and spaces sync.
# Touches: src/zen/spaces/ZenSpaceManager.mjs,
#          src/browser/base/content/zen-panels/popups.inc,
#          locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-workspaces.ftl.
# Applies on top of 0004 (same files).
